import seaborn as sns
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, classification_report

# Predict classes for test images
y_pred = cnn_model.predict(test_generator)
y_pred_classes = np.argmax(y_pred, axis=1)
true_classes = test_generator.classes

# Calculate confusion matrix
conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(true_classes, y_pred_classes)

# Plot heatmap of confusion matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.heatmap(conf_matrix, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='coolwarm', xticklabels=test_generator.class_indices.keys(), yticklabels=test_generator.class_indices.keys())
plt.xlabel('Predicted labels')
plt.ylabel('True labels')
plt.title('Confusion Matrix')
plt.show()

# Print classification report
print(classification_report(true_classes, y_pred_classes, target_names=test_generator.class_indices.keys()))

from keras.utils import load_img, img_to_array
import matplotlib.image as mpimg
# Path to the image you want to predict
image_path = 'test_ship_data/cruise_ship/11.jpg'

# Load and preprocess the image
img = load_img(image_path, target_size=(150, 150))
img_array = img_to_array(img)
img_array = np.expand_dims(img_array, axis=0)
img_array /= 255.  # Rescale pixel values to [0, 1]

# Make prediction
prediction = cnn_model.predict(img_array)

# Print the prediction probabilities
print("Prediction probabilities:", prediction)

# Get the predicted class
predicted_class = np.argmax(prediction)
img = mpimg.imread(image_path)
# Plot the image
plt.imshow(img)
plt.axis('off')  # Turn off axis
plt.show()

print("Predicted class Number:", predicted_class)
print("predicted_name :", rev_dict[predicted_class] )

MobileNet v2 customized model¶

In [150]:
from keras.applications import MobileNetV2
from keras.layers import GlobalAveragePooling2D, Dropout, Dense, BatchNormalization

# Load MobileNetV2-Light as the first layer
base_model = MobileNetV2(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(192, 192, 3))

# Freeze the MobileNetV2-Light layers
base_model.trainable = False

# Initialize the model
model = Sequential()

# Add MobileNetV2-Light as the first layer
model.add(base_model)

# Add GlobalAveragePooling2D layer
model.add(GlobalAveragePooling2D())

# Add Dropout layer
model.add(Dropout(0.2))

# Add Dense layer with 256 neurons and activation relu
model.add(Dense(256, activation='relu'))

# Add BatchNormalization layer
model.add(BatchNormalization())

# Add Dropout layer
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

# Add Dense layer with 128 neurons and activation relu
model.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))

# Add BatchNormalization layer
model.add(BatchNormalization())

# Add Dropout layer
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

# Add Dense layer with 9 neurons and activation softmax
model.add(Dense(9, activation='softmax'))

# Print model summary
model.summary()

from keras.utils import load_img, img_to_array
import matplotlib.image as mpimg
def predict_(subfolder, img_no):
    image_path = 'test_ship_data/' + subfolder + '/' + img_no +'.jpg'

    # Load and preprocess the image
    img = load_img(image_path, target_size=(192, 192))
    img_array = img_to_array(img)
    img_array = np.expand_dims(img_array, axis=0)
    img_array /= 255.  # Rescale pixel values to [0, 1]
    
    # Make prediction
    prediction = model.predict(img_array)
    
    # Print the prediction probabilities
    print("Prediction probabilities:", prediction[0])
    
    # Get the predicted class
    predicted_class = np.argmax(prediction)
    img = mpimg.imread(image_path)
    # Plot the image
    plt.imshow(img)
    plt.axis('off')  # Turn off axis
    plt.show()
    # Print the predicted class
    print("Predicted class Number:", predicted_class)
    print("predicted_name :", rev_dict[predicted_class] )
